overview: The user initiated a request for comprehensive browser-based testing
  of a sleep questionnaire application. The agent began by confirming the dev
  server was active and navigated to the application's main page. Upon
  encountering a multi-section questionnaire with active validation, the agent
  initially attempted to test validation by clicking "Next Section." When this
  didn't visually progress, the agent inspected the console for errors and
  reviewed the  source code to understand the form's
  structure and sections. To expedite testing, the agent decided to leverage a
  "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button to quickly generate a report, with
  plans to manually test the form flow later. This approach allowed for a
  quicker assessment of the report generation functionality.
